description: A freed rapist is loose on the streets of Seattle and Green Arrow is determined to find him...and Black Canary is equally committed to stopping the culprit...whatever the cost!
name: Predator Part 2

description: Sutton Mill, a small town in Washington, becomes the focal point of controversy as its council votes to make the town a sanctuary for draft resisters. Oliver Queen and Dinah Lance are there when the controversy explodes into violence. Part 1 of 2.
name: Signs of the Times

description: A protest rally against the possible reinstatement of the military draft becomes a "Pitchforks and Torches" demonstration that nearly tears apart a small town. Part 2 of 2.
name: Pitchforks & Torches

description:
Inheriting his mentor's longbow leads Green Arrow to a legacy of murder, degradation and extortion. Trying to rectify these crimes, Ollie learns the victim may have been Shado's father.

Note: Green Arrow is no longer labelled 'Suggested for Mature Readers.'
name: The Hunt for the Red Dragon Part 1

description: Oliver Queen begins his search for Shado by the request of Ronald Quaid.
name: The Hunt for the Red Dragon Part 2

description: Quaid has the advantage over Green Arrow and Shado, and the two must play a deadly game of survival for their lives.
name: The Hunt for the Red Dragon Part 3

description: Green Arrow and Shado combine forces in a veritable duel to the death with Quaid.
name: The Hunt for the Red Dragon Part 4

description: Homeless people are being murdered one by one, so Green Arrow must ferret out a brand-new kind of killer.
name: Bum Rap Part 1

description: A serial killer preying upon Seattle's homeless is seized upon by a congressional candidate as a campaign issue while a group of homeless people help Green Arrow figure out what the killer could possibly be after.
name: Bum Rap Part 2

description: The members of a major rock band are being murdered and Green Arrow gets caught in the middle as he investigates behind-the-scenes of the world of rock-and-roll.
name: Reunion Tour Part 1

description: Rock 'n' roll may live forever, but the Electric Unicorns certainly won't. Green Arrow and his new band of merry men - including Dinah Lance - must risk life and limb before the remaining members of the band are slaughtered.
name: Reunion Tour Part 2

description: A wild panther roams the streets of Seattle...a group of international poachers on the lookout...and animal rights activists wait in the wings. A beautiful, mysterious woman is behind the plot - with only Green Arrow standing in the middle.
name: Wild in the Streets

description: The mysterious legend of Shamanus is exposed by a Brazilian research biologist in search of a rare black panther...that's on a rampage through the streets of Seattle, and is about to rip out Green Arrow's throat!
name: Wild in the Sheets Part Two

description: A major crime lord is in a desperate fight to save his life, with a U.S. congressman the sole witness as Green Arrow faces a countdown to save the life of a Vietnam vet.
name: Trigger Part 1

description: A sniper and an underground agent attempt to stop a crime lord from revealing too much on the witness stand. It falls to Green Arrow to stop World War III from breaking out in Seattle. Meanwhile, Dinah plans a New Years party for Marianne who makes a resolution about her love life.
name: Trigger Part 2

description: Green Arrow and Speedy, who is now Arsenal, are reunited in this special oversized issue, as are Green Arrow and Shado. But Green Arrow and Black Canary are separated as Green Arrow's life is threatened by the Yakuza once more.
name: Auld Acquaintance

description: Trying to deal with being left by Dinah, Oliver distracts himself by investigating a possible terrorist camp. His partner in the case is trouble...paid assassin Eddie Fyres.
name: Killing Camp Part 1

description: Together in a survivalist boot camp, Green Arrow and assassin Eddie Fyres find that the survivalist leader is wanted by every government in the world...and is willing to kill Green Arrow in order to maintain his freedom!
name: Killing Camp Part 2

description: Ollie and hitman-for-hire Eddie Fyres have captured an internationally-wanted terrorist. The problem is, the CIA wants him too, and they don't care who they have to kill to get him.
name: Killing Camp Part 3

description: Green Arrow is caught between a rock and a hard place as two groups want to put him away for good - the local police and the CIA. One group wants him run out of town or thrown into jail. The other just wants him dead.
name: New Dogs, Old Tricks

description: Green Arrow's been framed for murder, but only he can track down the CIA killers who set him up!
name: New Dogs, Old Tricks Part 2

description: Green Arrow gets in the middle of a fight between Nuklon and Shrapnel in "Home Alki".
name: Home Alki

description: Green Arrow takes on Rival, a vigilante who's trained in the way of the bow and able to dodge Ollie's arrows.
name: Night of the Bow

description: Green Arrow's in Los Angeles on a killer's trail, a path which brings him into contact with the Huntress.
name: The Weight

description: There's little rest and relaxation for Ollie in Las Vegas when he's targeted by a group of assassins. Part 1 of 2.
name: Strange Attractions

description: Green Arrow and Deathstroke fight side by side in order to bring down a ruthless mob. Part 2 of 2.
name: Chaos Theory

description: Green Arrow's road trip brings him to Dallas and onto the trail of some stolen artifacts, not to mention into conflict with Catwoman.
name: The Sun Stolen by Midnight

description: Ollie's journey across the country after leaving Seattle finds him in New Orleans playing judge, jury and...executioner?!
name: The Man That Care Forgot

description: There's nothing like watching the JLA from the sidelines, not to mention getting your stuff stolen, to make an archer feel ineffective.
name: The Hero Descending

description: While in Gotham City, Green Arrow finds a kindred spirit in Anarky.
name: Forgotten Paths

description: A Zero Hour crossover issue. The conclusion to the Cross Roads story arc. Green Arrow is on the streets of Star City, when a Zero Hour time disruption splits him into two separate timelines. In the one, after he encounters one of the Street Demonz gang members, chases him down, catches him, and brings him to the cops. He escapes, Green Arrow gives chase, and the gangster grabs a woman hostage, The woman, though, is another gang member, and the two open fire on Green Arrow. He captures them both. In the second timeline, Green Arrow also chases the Street Demonz member in a different route. He meets the same female gang member, but in this continuity they kill Green Arrow. The timelines re-merge, and Green Arrow sees his dead counterpart. As Green Arrow examines his own dead body, Batman appears and recruits him to join the heroes in New York City.
name: He Who Hesitates

description: Oliver Queen and Connor Hawke are on the run from assassins in "Images". Part 1 of 5.
name: Images

description: Ollie recruits Eddie Fyers for help in figuring out who's after him, while Connor gets into a bind. Part 2 of 5.
name: Final Friends

description: Ollie, Fyers and Connor make an assault on the assassins' stronghold. Part 3 of 5.
name: Triple Threat

description: Ollie, Eddie and Connor continue to try to evade the hitmen on Ollie's trail. Part 4 of 5.
name: Mall of the Dead

description: Ollie has been captured and Eddie and Connor enlist the help of an enemy to try and track him down. Part 5 of 5.
name: The Truth Hurts

description: Ollie is recruited by the NSA and Connor and Eddie enlist an old friend to help find him.
name: Father's Day

description: Connor wants to save the ashram from being turned in to an amusement park and so he does a business man a favor by trying to solve his problems in Mexico.
name: Jaguar Moon

description: Connor faces off against a man-turned-god while in Mexico.
name: Gods and Tourists

description: Connor's mom has been kidnapped and he teams up with Kyle Rayner to find her.
name: Bad Blood

description: Connor teams up with Tim Drake to take down his arms-dealing step-dad.
name: Open Season

description: Connor works as a hired bodyguard while trying to earn money to save the ashram.
name: Enter the Roustabout

description: Connor continues working as a bodyguard.
name: Viva Los Dragons

description: Connor tries to find himself in Idaho by reconnecting with his grandfather. Meanwhile, Eddie tries to help an old friend in Metropolis.
name: Metropolis Confidential

description: Lois Lane agrees to help Green Arrow contact the last man to see Connor's father alive, but asks for a favor in return.
name: Trouble Town

description: Continued from GREEN LANTERN (1990-2004) #76. Continuing the search for Kyle's father, Green Lantern and Green Arrow return to the town of Desolation, where the townspeople have grown rich by suing corporations. Continued in GREEN LANTERN (1990-2004) #77.
name: Hard-Traveling Heroes: Next Generation part 2: Desolation Again

story_arc_credits.name: Hard Traveling Heroes: The Next Generation

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: Hard Traveling Heroes: The Next Generation

description: Continued from GREEN LANTERN (1990-2004) #77. Green Arrow must somehow convince Green Lantern that Kyle's father isn't what he appears as the duo tries to stop a deadly satellite from laying waste to the U.S.
name: Hard Traveling Heroes: The Next Generation part 4: Final Appeal

story_arc_credits.name: Hard Traveling Heroes: The Next Generation

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: Hard Traveling Heroes: The Next Generation

description: Connor is entrusted with an ancient map and so he and Eddie travel to China to find the city marked on it.
name: The Lotus Seed, Part One: Queen of the Shadows

description: Connor and Eddie arrive at an ancient city to return a package, but there may be more going on than either of them know.
name: The Lotus Seed, part two: The Sundered Soul

description: As temperatures plummet with the sun being blotted out in The Final Night, Eddie and Connor's plane, heading for Japan, is forced to make an emergency stop. While stopped Connor and Eddie help a village that is freezing escape.
name: The Thousand Year Night

description: "The Iron Death" part one of three. Eddie gets attacked while in Osaka, and given a choice: kill a target that his attackers choose or they kill Connor.
name: Discovering Japan

description:
"The Iron Death" Part 2 of 3. Eddie is sent to assassinate Dinah, but instead he chooses to team up with her. Then, Connor, Eddie, and Dinah encounter Shado and find out what is really going on behind the group responsible for the assassination attempt.

Note: The katakana used on the cover is incorrect, reading as "kreen" rather than "green"
name: A Gathering of Wolves

description: The conclusion to "The Iron Death". Connor, Eddie, Dinah, and Shado must race against the clock to stop a nuclear detonation.
name: The Death that Walks

description: "Endangered Species" part 1 of 2. After seeing a photograph of Ollie, Connor goes in search of his father in dangerous territories.
name: Dragon Country

description: "Endangered Species" Part 2. Connor is taken captive and Eddie has to figure out how to save him with a broken leg.
name: Empty Quest

description: As Connor and Eddie head out they run into a dangerous situation with a C.I.A. agent on the bus.
name: Menu for Disaster

description: Connor fights to reclaim the temple for Master Jansen but faces an unexpected foe.
name: The Monkey's Fist

description: "Stormbringers" part 1 of 2. After being defeated by Silver Monkey Connor and Master Jansen go to Idaho to visit Connor's grandfather. In Idaho, something mysterious is happening during a terrible drought.
name: Dry Bones

description: "Stormbringer" part 2 of 2. During a drought in Idaho there have been mysterious drownings. Connor reunites with an agent of the Mexican Federal Judiciary.
name: Immersed

description: Connor returns to New York to try and make amends with his mother, only to find she is still married to the arms dealer, Milo Armitage.
name: Stepfathers and Sons

description: Nicholas Kotero is planning revenge. Meanwhile, in New York, Connor comes under attack while shopping with his mom. Continued in Green Lantern #92.
name: The Fiery Furnace

description: Nicholas Kotero's plan to get revenge on Oliver Queen is coming to a head, and so Kyle and Connor have to race to stay one step ahead of him.
name: All Colors of Hate

description: Jansen is approached with a job offer, but he may have gotten himself in over his head.
name: Deadly Comrades part one: Capital Crimes

description: Master Jansen has been taken prisoner by the Russian mob for interfering with their extortion schemes. Now Connor must enter the thieves' den and save Jansen before it's too late.
name: Deadly Comrades, Part two: Theives' World

description: While on a vacation cruise with Kyle (Green Lantern) and Wally (The Flash), three villains seize the ship in hopes of reviving a greater evil.
name: Three of A Kind Part 2: Death at the Top of the World

description: Crackshot visits Connor in San Francisco. Meanwhile, Milo is back to the arms business while Sandra just wants to enjoy her vacation.
name: Guns and Butter

description: Connor is taken by surprise when Eddie Fyers suddenly blazes into his apartment after an apparent bout into outer space, and with newly gained superpowers.
name: Like A God, part one

description: The conclusion to "Like a God". The Justice League helps Connor save Eddie and stop the aliens who poisoned him.
name: Lest the Heavens Fall

description: Green Arrow is in Gotham on the trail of high-tech weapons dealers when he and Batman are targeted by the Brotherhood of the Monkey, looking to avenge the humiliating defeat of the Silver Monkey at Connor's hands!
name: Brotherhood of the Fist, Part One: The Stalkers

description: The epic battle comes to a head as Green Arrow faces off against the Paper Monkey, who is Lady Shiva! She is determined to kill Connor, who she has heard is a master martial artist, in order to retain the title of the world's best martial artist. Meanwhile, Eddie Fyers struggles against Deathstroke to free Black Canary and Bronze Tiger from the Monkey Cult!
name: Brotherhood of the Fist, Part 5: The Borrowed Life

description:
Connor Hawke teams up with Hal Jordan to try and stop the new Eden Corps.

Continued in Green Lantern #104
name: Greener Pastures, part one: In the Garden

description:
The West Coast Avengers are no more, but Iron Man has plans of his own for a new team, and a new philosophy! They will actively prevent disasters before they happen, rather than stopping them. They are…Force Works!

Iron Man, brings Spider-Woman, USAgent, Scarlet Witch, and Wonder Man together to form Force Works. He shows them there new headquarters, The Works. Everything seem to be going well but when Scarlet Witch and Wonder Man go back to the old Avengers West headquarters and run into Vision and the Black Widow, things go bad quickly.

The Kree attack the four heroes and use a ray to debilitate Vision and Wonder Man. Wonder Man takes off for the Kree's mother ship in orbit. The rest of the Force Works team shows up and Scarlet Witch uses her Hex powers, and they summon Century, who helps fight back the Kree.

In space Wonder Man turns off the Kree's ray, but when two space pods destroy the ship it appears that Wonder Man is killed. Back on earth more pods land near the Force Works team, and the Scatter emerge. They teleport away with Spider-Woman, USAgent and Scarlet Witch, leaving Iron Man, with a confused Century, wondering how everything went wrong so quickly.
name: Daybreak

description:
The unthinkable has happened - Wonder Man has fallen! And his replacement raises more questions than answers! Who is the enigmatic Century?

Iron Man meets the mysterious alien know as Century, and Force Works prepare to battle the Scatter.
name: Aftermath

description: Force Works' baptism of fire isn't over yet! The new team has their hands full when taking on a mysterious alien race known only as the Scatter!
name: Southern Showdown as FW Delivers Deathblow to the Alien Scatter!

description: Force Works is a long way from home helping to quell a Slorenian civil war, but the problems really being to flare up when the powerful and savage creature known as Ember joins the fray!
name: Ignition

description: The fight in Slorenia takes a surprising turn, when Force Works is suddenly betrayed by the Slorenian Black Brigade! Can the team survive a two-pronged atttack?
name: Enter: Black Brigade

description:
HANDS OF THE MANDARIN tie-in! The team faces off against the deadly forces of the Mandarin!

The Mandarin's new super-team attacks Force Works in Hong Kong. Seemingly, War Machine and Century are slain.
name: Hands of the Mandarin

description: HANDS OF THE MANDARIN tie-in! Force Works may be beaten, but not beaten down! The team rallies to once again fight off Mandarin's Avatars!
name: Hands of the Mandarin Part 4 of 6: Hearts of Darkness

description: The Force Works team finds themselves traveling down under to face a mysterious monster! But they won't be alone, as they're joined by a new hero: Dreamguard!
name: Terror Down Under! With Newcomer Dreamguard!

description: Force Works and Dreamguard continue their deadly battle with the creature known only as the Orphan! Plus, a who's who of Marvel heroes remembers their fallen comrade, Wonder Man.
name: Dancing With Demons

description: Black Brigade has returned, and he won't stop until he exacts his revenge on every member of Force Works! His first target - Julia Carpenter, aka Spider-Woman!
name: Red Heat!

description: The Slorenian villains continue their campaign of revenge on Force Works, until Iron Man decides it's time to get a little payback for the payback! Plus, a back up adventure starring War Machine!
name: Iron Man on the Savage Edge! Why?

description: Force Works teams up with Earth's Mightiest Heroes - the Avengers! The heroes take the fight to the Kree cabal called Starstealth, to get revenge for the death of Wonder Man!
name: War Crimes

description: The payback for Wonder Man comes down to this! The combined strength of Force Works and the Avengers against the alien might of the Kree enforcers known as Starstealth! Who will come out on top?
name: The Fires Of Sunrise

description: A mysterious new evil has attacked Force Works, and only US Agent and Century remain standing to save them! But can they even trust one another?
name: Lost & Found

description: Moonraker makes his first appearance, although everyone on the teams to know for quite some time, except for Rachel Carpenter who never remembers seeing him until this issue.
name: Traintor's Gate

description: Iron Man kills Amanda Chaney in this issue.
name: Mantis! Kang! ...the Hands Behind the Puppet!

description: In the aftermath of Avengers: Timeslide, Force Works faces the fact that the team is finished. But how will they respond to the Avenger's pressures?
name: Afterimage

description:
FINAL ISSUE! In the aftermath of "The Crossing," Force Works attempts to rebuild, but is the damage -- to the HQ, to the team, to their lives -- too much to repair? This concluding issue holds all the answers that will reverberate in upcoming issues of THE AVENGERS.

NOTE: The original solicitation had Heitor Oliveira as the penciler, of this issue.
name: Pain Threshold

description: After going against orders while stopping a terrorist attack in Mexico, Nick Fury gets demoted, and starts to feel that his old-school, cold war-methods are not appreciated in the new bureaucratic SHIELD. He wants to be back at war... Be careful what you wish for!
name: Part 1: Be Careful What You Wish for

description: Fury meets Dugan, who is now settled down, and is living a calm life with her non-smoking, anti-alcoholist wife. Meanwhile Ex-Hydra agent Gagarin occupies an island on the Pacific. It's up to Fury to stop him, but first he must fight the soft burocrats currently leading SHIELD.
name: Part 2: Apocalypse Shortly

description: Fury takes his place back as leader of SHIELD and begins military action against Napoleon Island.
name: Part 3: Here Comes the Pain

description: Gagarin's plan is starting to show: he removes the general taking control of the island himself, and he gets the U.S. in conflict with China, while also making the fight personal for Fury. But Fury starts executing his own plan for taking back the island.
name: Part 4: See You And Raise

description: Fury needs the General to give the world a false statement before the airstrike reaches the island: he needs to say Gagarin acted alone and he will surrender in 24 hours. But first the General wants Fury to get his daughters back from Gagarin.
name: Part 5: On Your Guns

description: That's it, Fury's mission failed, the air force started bombing the island, killing thousands. All Fury can do now is defeat the man responsible (in an extremely brutal fist-fight), and deal with the consequences of his failure.
name: Part 6: The Man Who Loved the War
The Hunt Begins...For The Truth!
... And Destroy!
